algorithm: Concatenation of STUDYID and SUBJID

label: Sequence Number
algorithm: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID in the domain.

label: Start Date/Time of Element
algorithm: If Element = SCREEN, derived from SVSTDTC where VISIT = SCREENING or from DS where DSDECOD\n= 'INFORMED CONSENT', whichever is earliest. If Element = EOS, derived from DS where DSCAT = DISPOSITION EVENT. For treatment\nElements, derived from first EXSTDTC for the element. For the complete algorithm see the referenced external document.

label: End Date/Time of Element
algorithm: If Element = SCREEN, derived from SVENDTC where VISIT = SCREENING. If Element = EOS,\nderived from DS where DSCAT = DISPOSITION EVENT or from the latest EXENDTC from EX whichever is later. For treatment Elements,\nderived from last EXENDTC for the element. For the complete algorithm see the referenced external document.

label: Planned Order of Elements within Arm

algorithm: Derived from ARM, ARMCD

label: Dose per Administration
algorithm: If ARMCD=WONDER10 then EXDOSE = Number of Tablets per Day (QVAL where QNAM=SMNO) * 10. If\nARMCD=WONDER20 then EXDOSE = Number of Tablets per Day (QVAL where QNAM=SMNO) * 20. If ARMCD=PLACEBO then EXDOSE = 0.

label: Dose Units
algorithm: Derived from ARM, ARMCD - equal to mg

label: Study Day of Start of Treatment
algorithm: EXSTDY = EXSTDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if EXSTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. EXSTDTC - RFSTDTC if\nEXSTDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

label: Study Day of End of Treatment
algorithm: EXENDY = EXENDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if EXENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. EXENDTC - RFSTDTC if EXENDTC\nprecedes RFSTDTC.
